Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.88,0:02:05.64,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Mother, father...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.13,0:02:07.77,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Mother, father...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.12,0:02:10.51,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Mother, father...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.63,0:02:12.52,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Mother, father...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.16,0:02:15.53,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Mother, father...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.53,0:02:18.11,Default,Michiyo,0000,0000,0000,,I could invite some of my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.33,0:02:19.44,FlashbackItalics,Michiyo,0000,0000,0000,,My friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.54,0:02:20.63,FlashbackItalics,Michiyo,0000,0000,0000,,My friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.72,0:02:21.87,FlashbackItalics,Michiyo,0000,0000,0000,,My friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.00,0:02:23.88,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.88,0:02:27.42,Default,Futari,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like Sis has friends of her own!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.96,0:02:32.42,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,I-I might not talk about them, \Nbut I've got lots of friends at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.42,0:02:33.54,Default,Futari,0000,0000,0000,,Lia—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.54,0:02:36.53,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't say that, even as a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.53,0:02:38.84,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,You should grow up to have \Nempathy for others.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.84,0:02:40.47,Default,Futari,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.43,0:02:43.53,Default,Michiyo,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like I should talk to my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.53,0:02:44.22,DefaultTop,Naoki,0000,0000,0000,,Me too—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.53,0:02:44.53,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,N-N-N—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.53,0:02:46.22,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, that's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.22,0:02:49.85,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,I've got lots of friends at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.85,0:02:50.52,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,S-See?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.52,0:02:53.36,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,You just wait for that concert!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.41,0:02:57.35,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have bragged like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.80,0:03:00.95,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,What do I do? If I don't find buyers \Nfor three more tickets...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.95,0:03:05.49,Signs,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(856,1)\fs12\fnArial Black\c&H111615&\bord2\4c&H835FCC&\shad1\3c&HE1E8E2&\frx54\fry28\pos(210.589,318.143)\frz10.01}Kessoku Band
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.03,0:03:06.96,DefaultItalicsTop,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,I made these promotional flyers to hand out \Naround my neighborhood, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.49,0:03:14.67,Signs,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\c&H111615&\fax0.1\bord2\4c&H835FCC&\shad1\3c&HE1E8E2&\pos(311.502,116.904)\frz11.69}Kessoku Band
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.49,0:03:14.67,Signs,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs10\c&H111615&\bord2\frz18.82\3c&HD8DEDA&\pos(433.35,320.795)}Mainly playing at clubs in the city
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.49,0:03:14.67,Signs,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs10\c&H111615&\bord2\frz18.82\3c&HD8DEDA&\pos(459.419,334.513)}Four-girl rock band
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.96,0:03:13.34,DefaultTop,Guitar Man,0000,0000,0000,,I read online that stuff with a handmade feel\Ncomes across as more charming!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.83,0:03:15.41,DefaultItalicsTop,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,But honestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.41,0:03:18.67,DefaultItalicsTop,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,How is someone with social anxiety \Nsupposed to hand out flyers?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.80,0:03:27.30,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,I feel so powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.76,0:03:30.14,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,I'm too scared to even move.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.65,0:03:37.19,Signs,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs14\c&H494C49&\pos(242.456,20.796)}Looks like lots of my friends are coming!\N\N\N\N\N\NThank goodness~~~~
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.00,0:03:37.54,DefaultItalics,Kita,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like lots of my friends \Nare coming! Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.32,0:03:38.44,Signs,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs14\c&H494C49&\pos(313.626,61.681)}I got 'em sold
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.54,0:03:38.93,DefaultItalics,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,I got 'em sold.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.61,0:03:43.74,Signs,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs14\fscx90\c&H494C49&\pos(197.311,19.203)}How are you doing, Bocchi-chan? Coming to practice today?\N\N\N\N\N\NI want to try the new song all together!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.93,0:03:41.65,DefaultItalics,Nijika,0000,0000,0000,,How are you doing, \NBocchi-chan? Coming today?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.65,0:03:44.32,DefaultItalics,Nijika,0000,0000,0000,,I want to try the new song all together!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.77,0:03:47.23,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Th-They're all taking care of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.23,0:03:49.16,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What do I say back?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.16,0:03:51.96,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,"I got that quota covered!" \Nand pretend I'm okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.96,0:03:55.36,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Or do I just admit, \N"I can't handle the quota!"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.36,0:03:56.84,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,But if I do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.24,0:03:59.67,Default,Nijika,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be in the band \Nif you can't handle your quota.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.67,0:04:01.42,Default,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,Bye-bye, Bocchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.42,0:04:03.08,Default,Kita,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.08,0:04:05.72,Default,Kita,0000,0000,0000,,I searched through my extensive connections
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.72,0:04:09.18,Default,Kita,0000,0000,0000,,and found us an amazing and \Ntotally extroverted guitarist!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.72,0:04:11.64,Default,Extroverted Guitarist,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.64,0:04:13.10,Default,Extroverted Guitarist,0000,0000,0000,,Rock you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.33,0:04:16.27,Default,Kita/Nijika/Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Rock you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.82,0:04:23.59,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Why couldn't I just accept my mom's help?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.21,0:04:31.24,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,A p-person's collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.24,0:04:33.42,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What do I do? I've got to say something...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.42,0:04:35.92,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I need an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.09,0:04:38.41,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.53,0:04:42.90,DefaultItalics,Smartphone,0000,0000,0000,,This is the news for 4:30 pm...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.90,0:04:45.38,Default,Kikuri,0000,0000,0000,,W-Water... Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.81,0:04:48.20,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right! I'll go buy some—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.20,0:04:50.08,Default,Kikuri,0000,0000,0000,,A-And hangover medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.08,0:04:50.92,Default,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.48,0:04:53.68,Default,Kikuri,0000,0000,0000,,And miso soup with clams...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.68,0:04:55.52,Default,Kikuri,0000,0000,0000,,And rice porridge too...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.98,0:05:00.39,Default,Kikuri,0000,0000,0000,,Preferably in a bed dressed with \Nfreshly line-dried sheets...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.39,0:05:02.94,DefaultItalics,Hitori,0000,0000,0000,,Sh-She's very demanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.79,0:05:18.38,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,I liked dark, cramped spaces,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.38,0:05:20.75,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,so I'd bury my face deep in my hood
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.75,0:05:23.13,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,My eyes resented the heartless world,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.13,0:05:26.88,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,but yearned for love
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.80,0:05:33.52,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,I liked being soaked by the rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.52,0:05:35.89,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,because my face looked better clouded over
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.89,0:05:38.53,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,I pretended to be afraid of the storm
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.53,0:05:41.36,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,while waiting for the sky to burst
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.47,0:05:48.32,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,Strum through the light's distortion
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.32,0:05:52.74,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to make thunder roar
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.74,0:05:58.54,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,Drum beyond the pain
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.54,0:06:02.67,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,What can I do? This fierce \Npounding is out of control
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.67,0:06:08.73,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,Strum in a harmonizing quartet
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.73,0:06:12.72,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to cause a revolution
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.72,0:06:18.73,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,Drum in a lamenting forte
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.73,0:06:23.48,Songs_OP,OP,0000,0000,0000,,What can I do? My savage \Nnature is beyond wild
